Media entrepreneur and Group CEO, RED | For Africa, Adebola Williams have been recognised for Outstanding Leadership Excellence at the 12th edition of the prestigious African Business Leadership Awards. Powered by the publication arm of the African Leadership Organisation, the African Leadership Magazine, the award aims to celebrate exceptional leadership in the African business ecosystem as well as phenomenal contributions to the continentâ€™s socio-economic growth and development. Williams received this award for his unique and inspirational contributions to business growth, job creation, youth empowerment, and wealth creation in the media and political space through the RED Group. He sits on the Global Champion council of the United Nations Generation Unlimited and is currently the Global patron of Malaria no More UK. Williams has also been the recipient of several national and international awards, including Young Global Leader by the World Economic Forum, Desmond Tutu Fellow by Africa Leadership Institute, the Emy African Young Achiever Award, the YouWin! Connect Award of Excellence, the Diamond Sabre Awards for Excellence in Public Relations in the C-Suite, the CNBC Africa Young Business Leader Awards, the Marketing Edge PR Person of the Year, and the Sabre Awards for superior achievement in Brand